@startuml
title Invite lifecycle — state machine (InviteStatus)

skinparam BackgroundColor #FAFAFA
skinparam state {
  BackgroundColor #FFFFFF
  BorderColor #1168bd
  ArrowColor #555
}

[*] --> Pending : CreateInviteHandler\n(landlord — RequireLandlord;\n7-day expiry, email sent via Hangfire)

Pending --> Accepted : AcceptInviteHandler\n(authenticated tenant; provisions the\nKeycloak user + creates the Lease — single tx)
Pending --> Rejected : RejectInviteHandler\n(anonymous)
Pending --> Expired : MarkExpiredInvitesJob\n(Hangfire, hourly; ExpiresAt < now)

Accepted --> [*] : terminal
Rejected --> [*] : terminal
Expired  --> [*] : OrphanCleanupJob\n(Hangfire, daily 03:00 UTC;\nhard-delete after 30 days if no lease)

note right of Pending
  Accept and Reject both require **Status == Pending AND not expired**,
  otherwise **404** (NotFoundException — there is deliberately no 410).
  The invite token is a 32-byte secret in the email link; the DB stores
  only its **SHA-256 hash**. Accept additionally requires:
   - the JWT **email to match** the invite email → else **403**
   - **no existing account** for that email → else **409** ("log in instead")
end note

note bottom of Expired
  Expired rows are kept ~30 days for audit, then hard-deleted by the
  orphan-cleanup scan **only** if no Lease was ever created from them.
  An accepted invite is retained as an immutable record of what was offered.
end note

@enduml
